{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionArtificial intelligence (AI) is transforming many industries, including health care.",
    "AI has the potential to revolutionize health care by enabling the detection of signs, patterns, diseases, anomalies, and risks.",
    "From administrative automation to clinical decision support, AI holds immense potential to improve patient outcomes, lower costs, and accelerate medical discoveries [1].",
    "An especially promising subset of AI is generative models, which are algorithms that can synthesize new data, imagery, text, and other content with humanlike creativity and nuance based on patterns learned from existing data [2].",
    "Generative AI could power clinical practices in health care, from generating synthetic patient data to augmenting rare disease research to creating AI-assisted drug discovery systems [3]."
  ]
}